\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The normal measurement of total pressure 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{t}=p+q$
\end_inset

 is obtained on the GV and C-130 and most other research aircraft by measuring
 the pressure delivered by a pitot tube aligned approximately along the
 airflow.
 This measurement is made by adding two measurements, one of ambient pressure
 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 (measured by a Parascientific Model 1000 absolute pressure transducer with
 measurement uncertainty 0.1
\begin_inset space \thinspace{}
\end_inset

